    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "I don't think that would work.\r\nIn my DOM I have a header and a container. Together it forms an accordion. So clicking on the header would open or close the accordeon.\r\n\r\nIn my JS, I have a loop that creates toggleRefinment Widgets and adds it to the container only when the count is > 0.\r\nBut in order not to show an empty accordion I would have to check if all toggleRefinment Widgets have a count that equals 0.\r\nBut I don't know how I can do this.",
